                "FRIND"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fractional independent yield for a given",
                "        mass chain"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Since the last members of the mass chains 101, 103,",
                " and 104 are either long lived or stable, their",
                " independent formations were assumed to be negligible",
                " and therefore the fractional independent yields (FIY)",
                " of 101Tc, 103Tc, and 104Tc were obtained as (1-FCY),",
                " where FCY refers to the fractional cumulative yield",
                " of precursor molybdenum. In the case of 105Tc, the",
                " FIY was obtained from the difference between the FCY's",
                " of 105Tc and 105Mo with the assumption that the chain",
                " terminates at 105Rh."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "1",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Standard deviation of average value based",
                " on 3 independent measurements. The following sources",
                " were taken into account:",
                " - chemical yield;",
                " - separation time;",
                " - counting statistics."
              ]
            }
          ],
